will be available to an international syndicate led by Merrill Lynch,
Barclays de Zoete Wedd and Credit Suisse First Boston.
Singer was listed on the New York Stock Exchange last August. Its shares
were trading at Dollars 20.25 each before yesterday's announcement.
Mr James Ting, Semi-Tech's chairman, said the proceeds would be used for
acquisitions to complement Singer's businesses. He said Semi-Tech had no
intention of further reducing its stake in Singer.
