FT  18 FEB 92 / International Company News: Storage Technology to acquire
distributor
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
STORAGE Technology, a US manufacturer of data storage sub-systems for
high-performance computers, announced yesterday that it planned to buy Edata
Scandinavia, its Scandinavian distributor, for Dollars 75m in cash.
Edata, which employs 194 people, had 1990 revenues of around Dollars 68.3m,
about three-quarters of it derived from Storage Technology products. It
operates in Belgium, Denmark, Finland, Luxembourg, the Netherlands, Norway
and Sweden. Storage Technology has European marketing operations in Austria,
France, Germany, Italy, Switzerland and the UK.
Mr Harris Ravine, Storage's executive vice-president for Europe, said the
acquisition would increase its direct presence on the continent. He added
that Edata in the past had concentrated on mainframe products, but in the
last two years it diversified into mid-range markets, which was in line with
Storage Technology's strategy.
The US company has reached an agreement with key Edata shareholders which
commits to its offer series A shares representing 70.4 per cent of the
votes, and it is making a public offer for the remainder of the equity.
