<HEADLINE>
FT  17 FEB 92 / Six arrested at M3 route protest
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SIX people were arrested yesterday when demonstrators chained themselves to
a crane being used to build an extension to the M3 motorway in a cutting
through wildlife-rich Twyford Down near Winchester.
About 300 objectors gathered for a rally close to the route of the proposed
extension. The six were later released pending a decision about them by
local senior police officers and the Crown Prosecution Service.
The European Commission has accused the government of failing to undertake a
proper environmental assessment of the route.
