<HEADLINE>
FT  17 FEB 92 / Boost seen for liability insurance
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
DIRECTORS and senior managers of UK companies are becoming more aware of
their potential personal legal liabilities when their businesses go wrong,
according to a survey published today by Wyatt Company, management
consultants.
The survey shows a sharp increase in the use of directors and officers (D&amp;O)
insurance, policies which cover directors and officers or senior managers
for the cost of legal awards made against them.
Wyatt, on the basis of a questionnaire sent to 109 companies, found that 62
per cent of industrial companies have D&amp;O cover compared with 26 per cent in
1989. One in four financial-sector companies also have coverage, against 17
per cent in 1989.
Mr Pierre Laurin, a director of Wyatt, said awareness had been assisted by
recent high-profile cases, including a number in which directors had been
found liable under the Insolvency Act 1986 for breach of fiduciary duties.
</TEXT>
